{"type":"message","id":"c85d3890","parentId":"eba5238c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T13:08:24.528Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Only 58 lines - well under 3000. No trimming needed. The file looks good.","thinkingSignature":"f41849eb08c69f41d4bc5e07a4c12d5d068080b0bb00f6441d8ebdee3bac47d9"},{"type":"text","text":"Only 58 lines — well under the 3000-line cap. Done.\n\n**Summary of today's arxiv check (2026-03-23):**\n\nThis was a solid week. March 19-20 had a big submission batch. Notable finds:\n\n- **Kumiho** (memory arch) — graph-native cognitive memory with formal AGM belief revision, 93.3% on LoCoMo-Plus vs Gemini 2.5 Pro's 45.7%. Best overall find.\n- **Path-Constrained MoE** — new angle on MoE routing by sharing params across layers; eliminates load balancing losses. Good fundamental read.\n- **DyMoE + AIMER** — both solid MoE papers on edge inference and pruning respectively.\n- **KaCGM** — KANs + causal generative models; interesting intersection of interpretability + causal.\n- **Utility-Guided Agent Orchestration** — explicit quality/cost tradeoff framework for tool-using agents.\n- **The Verifier Tax** — sobering results on safety enforcement in agents; SSR <5% despite catching 94% of unsafe actions.\n- **Time, Identity and Consciousness in LLM Agents** — Stack Theory applied to agent identity; separates \"talking like a self\" from \"being organized like one.\"\n\nAll written to `memory/arxiv-daily.md` under the 2026-03-23 section. File is at 58 lines — no trimming needed."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40953,"output":320,"cacheRead":11757,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53030,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774271295746}}
